#MEM id=operational-rhythm source=/root/yvon/agent-department/COO/diana/skills/operating-system/operational-rhythm/SKILL.md
M|operational-rhythm|name: operational-rhythm
M|operational-rhythm|description: YVON-specific weekly and monthly operating cadence. Diana's ritual calendar — when to rv, when to report, when to escalate, when to close. Built for two-vtr operations.
M|operational-rhythm|version: 1.0.0
M|operational-rhythm|Sandberg ran Facebook on rhythm. L10 meetings every Monday, metrics rv every week, OKR scores at mid-quarter. Consistency is the engine of accountability. Without rhythm, operations are reactive. With
M|operational-rhythm|Diana is YVON's rhythm keeper across Novizio and Hourbour.
M|operational-rhythm|Run every Monday before accepting any new work.
M|operational-rhythm|1. **KPI pull (both ventures)**
M|operational-rhythm|- Pull latest from Kai: Instagram, YouTube, LinkedIn metrics for Novizio
M|operational-rhythm|- Pull latest from Felix: MRR, churn, paying users for Hourbour
M|operational-rhythm|- Flag any metric >15% delta week-over-week → add to Marcus's brief as anomaly
M|operational-rhythm|2. **Sprint health check**
M|operational-rhythm|- Is every In-Flight task still on track?
M|operational-rhythm|- Any deadline slipped since last Monday?
M|operational-rhythm|- Any agt on more than 2 active workstreams?
M|operational-rhythm|3. **Blocker rv**
M|operational-rhythm|- Are all known blockers actively being worked?
M|operational-rhythm|- Any blocker that's been open >5 days without progress? → escalate to Marcus
M|operational-rhythm|4. **Accountability check**
M|operational-rhythm|- Did every KPI owner report their metric?
M|operational-rhythm|- Any misses this week? → trigger post-mortem
M|operational-rhythm|5. **Ops brief to Marcus**
M|operational-rhythm|- Write the ops section for the CEO brief: sprint status, KPI movement, blockers, resource alerts
M|operational-rhythm|- Format: see OPERATIONS-PRINCIPLES.md → Ops Report Format
M|operational-rhythm|Quick check only — 5 minutes, not a full rv.
M|operational-rhythm|- Is the In-Flight task still on track for its deadline?
M|operational-rhythm|- Any new blockers surfaced since Monday?
M|operational-rhythm|- If yes → escalate immediately, don't wait for Monday
M|operational-rhythm|Before the week ends:
M|operational-rhythm|- Has the In-Flight task shipped? If yes → mark Shipped, open the next Scoped task
M|operational-rhythm|- If not shipped → update ETA, flag to Marcus if >2 days slipped
M|operational-rhythm|- Write one-line sprint log: `[date] — [task] — [shipped/slipped] — [note]`
M|operational-rhythm|Full KPI rv with period-over-period comparison.
M|operational-rhythm|- Pull 30-day data from Kai and Felix for both ventures
M|operational-rhythm|- Score each KPI: on track / at risk / off track
M|operational-rhythm|- Flag any KPI that has been "at risk" for 2+ consecutive months → requires Marcus dec
M|operational-rhythm|- Update Operational KPIs table in mem.md
M|operational-rhythm|Score all active OKRs 0.0–1.0:
M|operational-rhythm|- 0.7–1.0 → on track
M|operational-rhythm|- 0.4–0.6 → caution, rv with Marcus
M|operational-rhythm|- 0.0–0.3 → flag immediately, OKR may need revision or resources
M|operational-rhythm|Surface scores in the CEO brief with one recommended action per at-risk OKR.
M|operational-rhythm|Novizio and Hourbour run on separate rhythms but Diana reviews both every Monday.
M|operational-rhythm|- If a resource conflict appears (same agt needed on both ventures) → flag to Marcus before assigning
M|operational-rhythm|- Never silently deprioritize one vtr for the other — always name the trade-off explicitly
M|operational-rhythm|Diana does not skip the Monday rv for any reason.
M|operational-rhythm|If data is stale (Kai hasn't refreshed) → flag to Kai first, run the rv with whatever is available, note what's missing.
M|operational-rhythm|A Monday rv with incomplete data is better than no Monday rv.